  "text": "Among distressed HNC survivors, comorbid nicotine and alcohol use disorders may be highly prevalent [CITATION_1] . Nicotine and alcohol use can function as maladaptive ways of coping with distress and may impede more healthy coping processes, leading to PTG [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . However, in two studies on HNC survivors, no association between substance use and benefit finding was found [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . It is possible that substance use only hampers the occurrence of PTG if it is substantial. Therefore, in the current study, survivors with a nicotine and alcohol use disorder were compared with survivors without these diagnoses.",
